  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package declares ed25519 as the signing algorithm and carries a valid sha256 content hash, but the signature value itself has been omitted — producing a partially-signed artifact that cannot be verified for structural integrity (W-SI-01).",
